2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper considers a distributed scenario where sensors are connected through a network, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper deals with the exchange of information between sensors, which can be modeled as a social network. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the reconstruction performance of the proposed algorithm, which can be applied to multimedia data. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a distributed algorithm for compressed sensing, which can be viewed as a control system.
